This paper focuses on privacy-preserving techniques for location data, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a statistical metric and model for generating fake location traces, which involves data analysis and machine learning techniques, making it relevant to the sub-categories of databases (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
